==Italian==
===Possessive adjective===
(''before the noun''): '''il suo''' ''m'' (''f'' '''la sua''', ''m plural'' '''i suoi''', ''f plural'' '''le sue''')<br>
(''after the noun; also used before a noun denoting a close family member''): '''suo''' ''m'' (''f'' '''sua''', ''m plural'' '''suoi''', ''f plural'' '''sue''')

#[[his]], [[her]], [[its]]
#:''i suoi figli'' - his/her/its children<!--masculine plural example before noun-->
#:''le sue macchine'' - his/her/its cars<!--feminine plural example before noun-->
#:''casa sua'' - his/her/its house<!--feminine singular example after noun-->
#:''suo padre'' - his/her/its father<!--masculine singular example before close family member-->
#(''often capitalised'') [[your]] (''polite singular form'')
#:''i Suoi figli'' - your children<!--masculine plural example before noun-->
#:''le Sue macchine'' - your cars<!--feminine plural example before noun-->
#:''casa Sua'' - your house<!--feminine singular example after noun-->
#:''Suo padre'' - your father<!--masculine singular example before close family member-->

